Given a positive integer N, find sum of its digits.


Input Format
The first and only line of input will contain a single integer N.

Output Format
Output on a single line: the sum of digits of ğ‘.


Sample 1:
Input             Output
87431              23





#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n,sum=0;
    scanf("%d", &n);
    for (int i=n;i>0;i/=10){
        sum = sum + (i%10);
    }
    printf("%d",sum);
}
